## Proposed Changes

### Frontend — TokenPayment Page

#### [MODIFY] [TokenPayment.jsx](file:///c:/Users/hp/Desktop/work/Karaya_Bandhu_Customer_frontend/frontend/src/pages/TokenPayment.jsx)

**Problem**: The back button (`navigate(-1)`) goes to whichever page was previous in browser history, which might be the booking page where draft data was cleared. Also, if the user already paid, they can still see this page and attempt payment again.

**Changes**:
1. **Persist `bookingId` to `sessionStorage`** so it survives page refresh and back navigation (not just `location.state`)
2. **Check booking status on mount** — if already `paid`, redirect to `search-provider` instead of showing payment form again  
3. **Replace `navigate(-1)` back button** with explicit `navigate(`/booking/${serviceId}`)` pointing to the BookingPage, or redirect home if already paid
4. **After successful payment, use `navigate(..., { replace: true })`** so the back button from SearchProviderPage doesn't return to the payment page

---

### Frontend — BookingPage

#### [MODIFY] [BookingPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/hp/Desktop/work/Karaya_Bandhu_Customer_frontend/frontend/src/pages/BookingPage.jsx)

**Problem**: Draft is cleared immediately on submit (line 400), before user has even paid. If user navigates back, all form data is lost.

**Changes**:
1. **Don't clear the draft on booking submission** — instead, save the `bookingId` alongside the draft data so we know a booking was already created
2. **On mount, check if a pending/unpaid booking already exists** for this service — if so, restore the draft data and redirect to token-payment instead of allowing a duplicate booking
3. **Clear the draft only after successful payment** (will be triggered via a flag check or after payment confirmation)
4. **Save `bookingId` into the session draft** so back-navigation knows the booking already exists

---

### Frontend — Post-Payment Cleanup

#### [MODIFY] [TokenPayment.jsx](file:///c:/Users/hp/Desktop/work/Karaya_Bandhu_Customer_frontend/frontend/src/pages/TokenPayment.jsx)

After successful payment (in the Razorpay handler and wallet handler):
1. **Clear the booking draft** from `sessionStorage` for the corresponding service
2. **Clear the persisted `bookingId`** from `sessionStorage`
3. **Navigate with `replace: true`** to prevent back-button return to payment page

---

### Summary of Session Storage Keys

| Key | Purpose | Set When | Cleared When |
|---|---|---|---|
| `booking_draft_{serviceId}` | Form data + selectedAddOns + bookingId | On form change & after booking creation | After successful payment |
| `pending_booking_{serviceId}` | Maps serviceId → bookingId for unpaid bookings | After `bookService()` succeeds | After successful payment |

